# Repo Standards

## Project Context
This is a project supporting real financial sector features

## Stack
* Database: PostgreSQL
* Backend: Spring Boot, Maven, Lombok, Logback SLF4J, Micrometer Tracing Bridge OTel
* Frontend: React Native
* Local deployment: Docker compose
* AWS deployment: GitHub Actions, Terraform, EKS Fargate, Amplify Hosting, RDS PostgreSQL, CloudWatch Logs

## Coding Standards
* Base monorepo structure: monorepo/
  * .github/workflows
    * deploy-backend.yml
    * deploy-frontend.yml
    * deploy-infra.yml
  * backend/
    * k8s/
    * src/
    * .dockerignore
    * Dockerfile
    * pom.xml
  * frontend/
  * infra/
  * docker-compose.yml
  * README.md
* Variables: single-source-of-truth variables: no redundant values
  * GitHub Actions variables and secrets: developer-chosen inputs used by GitHub Workflows
  * AWS SSM Parameter Store: outputs from Infra GitHub Workflow used by other GitHub Workflows. SSM_PARAM_PREFIX as explicit prefix
  * default spring boot properties for local deployment
* frontend
  * create frontend/package-lock.json before CD pipelines: cd frontend && docker run --rm -v "$PWD:/app" -w /app node:20-alpine npm install
* backend
  * Use java records where possible
  * application.yml
    * default values for developing environment
    * production-environment-first: development environment with single env var specifying the local profile, additional application-local.yml
    * lombok: @Value and @Qualifier as copyable annotations.
    * jackson.deserialization.fail-on-unknown-properties: false
  * NFR
    * Usability: HATEOAS API
    * Maintainability and testability:
      * Screaming Architecture and Clean Architecture
        ```
        src/main/
        |-- java/com/example/MY_PROJECT/
        |   |-- Application.java
        |   |-- BUSINESS_FEATURE/
        |   |   |-- domain/
        |   |   |   |-- entity/
        |   |   |   |   |-- Feature.java
        |   |   |   |-- gateway/
        |   |   |       |-- FeatureGateway.java
        |   |   |-- application/
        |   |   |   |-- usecase/
        |   |   |       |-- FeatureUseCase.java
        |   |   |-- infrastructure/
        |   |       |-- controller/
        |   |       |   |-- TECHNOLOGY/
        |   |       |       |-- TechnologyFeatureController.java
        |   |       |-- gatewayadapter/
        |   |       |   |-- TECHNOLOGY/
        |   |       |       |-- TechnologyFeatureAdapter.java
        |   |       |-- config/
        |   |       |-- interceptor/
        |   |       |-- filter/
        |   |-- shared/
        |       |-- CONCERN/
        |       |   |-- CLEAN_ARCHITECTURE_LAYERS/
        |       |-- unbounded_concerns/
        |           |-- CLEAN_ARCHITECTURE_LAYERS/
        |-- resources/
            |-- application.yml
        ```

        shared concerns example:
        ```
        src/main/
        |-- java/com/example/MY_PROJECT/
            |-- shared/
                |-- log/
                |   |-- domain/
                |   |   |-- entity/LogPayload.java
                |   |   |-- gateway/LogGateway.java
                |   |-- infrastructure/
                |       |-- gatewayadapter/slf4j/Slf4jLogAdapter.java
                |       |-- filter/RequestLoggingFilter.java
                |-- exception/
                    |-- domain/entity/ServletResponseException.java
                    |-- infrastructure/interceptor/GlobalExceptionHandler.java
        ```
      * observability
        * pod CPU/memory metrics
        * log entry with
          * timestamp
          * level
          * service_name
          * thread_name
          * traceId
          * logger_name
          * message
          * structuredArguments: LogPayload with URL and body, response status and body, duration
          * stackTrace
        * logback with JSON encoder, SLF4JLogAdapter with SLF4J and LogPayload
        * logging in Controllers, RestControllerAdvice, external services requests
    * Portability: docker containers
    * Availability: scalability / resilience / reliability
      * RestControllerAdvice
      * custom ServletResponseException extending RuntimeException with status and a second constructor with cause Throwable
      * ErrorResponse with status, message, errors
      * fargate multi-az
      * k8s liveness/readiness probes
      * Performance
        * no stack trace in info logs
        * OncePerRequestFilter with @Order(Ordered.HIGHEST_PRECEDENCE)
        * close no longer needed Closeable resources
        * pagination
    * security
      * AWS Secrets Manager SDK for reading secrets from the backend
      * eks-pod-identity for authorization to AWS resources
      * user credentials on request headers, not on body which is logged
      * BOLA-proof
        * UUIDs as db records id
* infra
  * vpc.tf:
    * single_nat_gateway = false
    * one_nat_gateway_per_az = true
